President Obama called President Hadi of Yemen to express the United States' support for his government and the people of Yemen as they work towards political and economic reform. They discussed the recent violence in Yemen and the importance of President Hadi's leadership in achieving meaningful change. President Obama congratulated President Hadi on the nomination of a new Prime Minister and expressed support for his efforts to implement the peace agreement and recommendations of the National Dialogue. The Presidents agreed on the need for all parties to deescalate the conflict, form a representative government, and implement the transition. They also reiterated their commitment to countering the threat posed by al-Qa'ida in the Arabian Peninsula.